President Biden has announced three new nominees for U.S. Attorneys and one new nominee for U.S. Marshal. These officials are chosen for their dedication to enforcing the law, professionalism, experience, commitment to equal justice, and the independence of the Department of Justice. The President has proposed a budget that increases funding for law enforcement to address the rising crime rate. He has also launched efforts to address gun crime by increasing police presence, supporting prevention programs, and cracking down on illegal gun trafficking. The President has announced a total of 56 nominees for U.S. Attorneys and 12 nominees for U.S. Marshals. The nominees for U.S. Attorneys are Casey T. Arrowood, Henry C. Leventis, and Kevin G. Ritz. The nominee for U.S. Marshal is William Ryan Hart.